Class CrimeDataLoadingFragment.CrimeDataLoadingAsyncTaskHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • benak.tomas.crimemonitor.client.CrimeDataLoadingFragment.CrimeDataLoadingAsyncTaskHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AsyncTaskHandler<CrimeResultData>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CrimeDetailLoadingFragment.CrimeDetailLoadingAsyncTaskHandler, CrimeListLoadingFragment.CrimeListLoadingAsyncTaskHandler, CrimeSummaryLoadingFragment.CrimesSummaryAsyncTaskHandler, UtvarDetailLoadingFragment.UtvarDetailAsyncTaskHandler
    Enclosing class:
    CrimeDataLoadingFragment<CrimeResultData extends UtvarAndIntervalBasedCrimeSummary & java.io.Serializable>

    protected class CrimeDataLoadingFragment.CrimeDataLoadingAsyncTaskHandler
extends java.lang.Object
implements AsyncTaskHandler<CrimeResultData>
    CrimeDataLoadingAsyncTaskHandler is the abstract helper class to wrap and handle the instance of GetCrimeDataTask for the CrimeDataLoadingFragment fragment.

    This class is an AsyncTaskHandler, which means it listens for the lifecycle callbacks of the wrapped GetCrimeDataTask and calls the callback methods in this fragment if appropriate.

    There only is at most one instance of this class for the CrimeDataLoadingFragment at any point.

    For each crime data loading task request there is a new instance of this class to wrap it.

    For the technical reasons this class also stores the Location instance which is a location of the department code, for which the crime data is to be loaded. It is mainly in order for this location object to be reported back in one of the CrimeDataLoadingListener callbacks.

    Author:
    Tom

      • onPostExecute

        public void onPostExecute(CrimeResultData result)
        Called when the wrapped task calls its AsyncTask.onPostExecute.

        The owning fragment is notified.

        • If there was an error, the owning fragment's CrimeDataLoadingFragment.onCrimeDataLoadingError is called.
        • If an empty result was retrieved, the owning fragment's CrimeDataLoadingFragment.onCrimeEmptyDataLoaded is called.
        • If the crime data was successfuly loaded, the owning fragment's CrimeDataLoadingFragment.onCrimeDataLoaded is called.

        Specified by:
